<h2 class="project__step-title">Developer Features</h2>
<div class="side-by-side">
  <div>
    <p>
      As a remote studio, Midnight Society's developers aren't often in the same
      room. That's why for their big snapshot event for fans, it was essential
      to be on location with the developers in a rare meetup, to sit down with
      them on-camera, hear them explain the features of their game, and edit
      their interviews into features for the big night. Day 1 consisted of
      sit-downs and editing the raw interviews. On Day 2, I designed motion
      graphics and worked with the developers to capture in-game footage.
    </p>
    <p>
      In just a few days, I was able to execute a full video package, along with
      motion design, social assets to promote the live broadcast, and graphics
      for the arena. The event, with presenting sponsor Cheez-It, was a huge
      success, with thousands of fans filling the arena to see new features
      unveiled, watch influencers compete on the big stage, and get their hands
      on the game at demo stations.
    </p>
  </div>

